Rating: 0
This is the best applesauce I've had. I cut the sugar in half, and like other users, added a half cup of water in the beginning to prevent burning. I omitted the cinnamon and added the zest from a medium orange and a teaspoon of vanilla. Phenomenal!! For some reason couldn't get a 4 fork, but if I could I'd give it a 5.

Rating: 4
Excellent and easy to make. The color is wonderful and much better than the brownish version we get with other recipes. My 6 yr old loved it! And it's good for your kidney's because of the cranberries. I only made one slight change: I added 1 Tbsp of water to pot at the start to avoid having apples stick to bottom of the pot.

