God I loved this. I used a mix of apples from the farmer's market and fresh cranberries from Whole Foods. It was delicious, and the prettiest red.

Rating: 3
Cranberries make an excellent addition to applesauce. I will confess that I used 4 lbs of whatever apples I had on hand - not golden delicious (probably a mix of gala and honeycrisp). I also had to add 1/2 cup of water at the beginning so the sugar would stop burning. Overall, though, very delicious.